{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix M2AP SCTP data handling memory management and error reporting\n\n### Summary\nWhen processing M2AP messages over SCTP, the `m2ap_eNB_handle_sctp_data_ind` function was using an incorrect task identifier when freeing received message buffers. This caused memory management issues and potential crashes under load.\n\nAdditionally, the function did not check the return value from `m2ap_eNB_handle_message`, leading to silent failures when message processing failed.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_eNB.c`: \n  - Changed `itti_free(TASK_UNKNOWN, sctp_data_ind->buffer)` to `itti_free(TASK_M2AP_ENB, sctp_data_ind->buffer)` in `m2ap_eNB_handle_sctp_data_ind`\n  - Added error checking for `m2ap_eNB_handle_message` return value with proper logging\n  - Various whitespace changes due to editor formatting (no functional impact)\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy M2AP traffic conditions, observe memory corruption errors or crashes in the M2AP task. Error logs may show \"Failed to free memory\" messages when the incorrect task identifier is used for buffer deallocation.\n\nThe issue is most reproducible when the eNB is handling multiple M2 connections simultaneously and processing a high volume of M2AP messages.\n"
}